Explanation:
The solution uses bit manipulation to check if a number is a power of four without using loops or recursion. The expression (n & (n - 1)) == 0 checks if the number is divisible by all its previous powers of 4 (i.e., if it is a power of four). The bitwise AND operator (&) checks for the presence of a bit, and subtracting 1 from n removes the current number itself from the check. Since the operation has a constant time complexity, the solution is efficient.

